# Day 2 – ADF UI Deep Dive

## ✔ What I Learned
- Azure Data Factory has 3 main sections:
  1. Author – used to create pipelines, datasets, linked services.
  2. Monitor – used to check pipeline runs and failures.
  3. Manage – used to configure linked services and integration runtime.
- Learned basic pipeline components (Pipeline, Activities, Dataset, Linked Service, Trigger).
## ✔ UI Map (Simple)
Author → Build pipelines  
Monitor → See logs  
Manage → Set connections  

## ✔ Why This Matters
Knowing the ADF layout helps me build and troubleshoot pipelines easily.
